President Donald J. Trump has been addressing the failures of Obamacare by implementing measures to bring back flexibility and affordability to American health insurance. His administration is working to expand insurance options, providing affordable and flexible choices for millions of Americans. Additionally, President Trump aims to improve drug affordability and access, making prescription drugs more accessible and affordable for those in need. He is also taking action to combat the opioid crisis, which has been plaguing communities across the United States.